  "prompt": "What will be my rank I scored 325 in neet?",
  "response": "Predicting your exact rank in NEET (National Eligibility cum Entrance Test) based solely on your score can be challenging because ranks are influenced by several factors, including:\n\n1. The overall difficulty of the exam in the year you took it.\n2. The performance of other candidates (how many scored higher or lower than you).\n3. The normalization process employed by the exam authorities.\n4. Category-specific variations (if you belong to a reserved category like SC, ST, OBC, EWS, etc.).\n\nHowever, based on past trends, a score of 325 typically places you around a moderate rank, potentially ranging from 180,000 to 250,000. This estimation is based on general patterns observed in past years and can vary significantly.\n\nTo get a more precise idea, you should wait for the official rank list to be released by the exam authorities. Good luck!",
